<a href="#0" id="0">As the beginning event of a scenario, we extracted nouns that describe social problems ( social problem nouns , e.g., deforestation ) from Wikipedia to focus our evaluation on the ability to generate scenarios about them, which is a realistic use-case of scenario generation.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">We extracted 557 social problem nouns and used the cause phrases of the event causality candidates that consisted of one of the social problem nouns as the scenario ’ s beginning event.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">We applied our event causality extraction method to 2,451,254 candidates (Section 3.1 ) and culled the top 1,200,000 phrase pairs from them (See Section LABEL:A-sec:examples-of-event-causality in the supplementary notes for examples.</a>
